= Alpha Roadmap & Success Criteria (v1.0) =

This document defines the transition from **POC (v2.10)** to **Alpha (v2.11+)** and the remaining milestones for the FactHarbor v1.0 release.

== Current Status: Alpha (v2.11.0) ==

The system has successfully transitioned to the **ClaimAssessmentBoundary (CB)** architecture. The legacy Orchestrated pipeline has been removed.

=== Completed Milestones (Alpha Entry) ===
* **CB Pipeline Implementation:** 5-stage sequential flow operational.
* **Evidence-Emergent Boundaries:** Manual "AnalysisContext" framing removed.
* **Multi-Provider Search:** Brave, Google, and Bing fallback logic implemented.
* **Source Reliability v2:** LLM-powered reliability assessment instead of keyword-based.
* **Quality Gates:** Gate 1 (Fidelity) and Gate 4 (Confidence) enforced.

== Roadmap to Beta (Q2 2026) ==

The following features are prioritized for the next major milestone.

=== 1. Metric Maturation ===
* **TIGERScore Integration:** Automated evaluation of **T**ruth, **I**nsight, **G**rounding, **E**vidence, and **R**elevance.
* **AlignScore:** Measuring alignment between extracted claims and final verdicts.
* **Refinement:** Transitioning from diagnostic heuristics to robust model-based metrics.

=== 2. Cross-Lingual Robustness ===
* **Validation:** Ensuring Stage 1 (Extraction) and Stage 4 (Verdict) perform equally well in DE, FR, PT, and ES.
* **Constraint:** Meaning over wording (no English-only semantic assumptions).

=== 3. Performance & Cost Optimization ===
* **Haiku 4.5 Tiering:** Moving non-critical classification tasks to lighter models.
* **Caching:** Aggressive search and LLM result caching.

== Success Criteria (v1.0 Release) ==

| Dimension | Target Metric | Status |
|-----------|---------------|--------|
| **Accuracy** | >92% Factually Correct | In Progress |
| **Neutrality** | <4% Bias Asymmetry | Testing (test:neutrality) |
| **Reliability** | >85% Confidence in High-Probative Verdicts | In Progress |
| **Coverage** | Supports 5+ languages out-of-the-box | In Progress |

